         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">25, WILTON PLACE. S.W. ¶ Feby 10 1874 ¶ My dear Sir ¶  ¶ Many thanks for your kind letter of the 1st Decr containing the intimation that you had obtained the authority for the £100 for the next and la...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">74.02.10</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From George Bentham</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M3, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times, Times; ">25, WILTON PLACE. S.W.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Feby 10 1874</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Many thanks for your kind letter of the 1st Decr containing the intimation that you had obtained the authority for the £100 for the next and last volume of the Flora Australiensis which I hope I may be enabled to finish If I do not hear from the Agent General after next mail I will as you recommend apply to him</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have finished the Brasilian <name key="Mimoseae">Mimoseae</name>
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The final part of Bentham (1859-76), 'Leguminosae, III: <name key="Mimoseae">Mimoseae</name>', was published on 1 July 1876 as vol. 15, part 2, pp. 257–504.</p>
               </note> and am now at Genera Plantarum<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83).</p>
               </note> and hope to be at Flora Australiensis in the autumn I should therefore be much obliged to you to send me the Monocotyledons in the course of the summer I will take care to leave a Memorandum under which the £100 will be returned if I do not live to finish the volume.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I resigned the Presidency of the Linnean Society last week. My successor is not yet fixed upon. By custom he will be a Zoologist<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bentham's successor was George James Allman (Gage &amp; Stearn (1988), p. 219). </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your specimens of <name key="MacGregoria">MacGregoria</name> had somehow been laid aside and forgotten, they will be immediately looked out in the mean time what you have sent to Dr Masters show it to be a new genus of undoubted <name key="Stackhousieae">Stackhousieae</name>
               <note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M had repeatedly requested the views of the Kew botanists on this plant; see, for example, M to J. Hooker, 8 September 1873 (in this edition as 73-09-08a). M erected the genus (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">M. racemigera</seg>) in B74.04.01, p. 161. It was illustrated, with a short text by Bentham, in Hooker (1867-89), vol. 13, pp. 23-4, plate 1230.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I sincerely trust you may now be going on more comfortably and able to devote yourself as steadily and successfully to science as you have done hitherto</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Yours most truly</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>George Bentham</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="MacGregoria">MacGregoria</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Mimoseae">Mimoseae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Stackhousieae">Stackhousieae</name>
            </p>
         </div>
